Full Description: Bane Machinery traces its beginnings to 1963 when George P. Bane purchased Texas Tractor Company in Tyler, Texas. He gave the new company his name, George P. Bane, Inc., and his commitment to provide outstanding construction equipment and dependable service to his customers. Within a few years George P. Bane II had joined his father and learned the business firsthand by working in every critical department—sales, service, and parts. In 1980, the son succeeded his father as president of the company. Eight years later, he opened a second location in Dallas. Scott and Phil Bane are the third generation of Banes to join the family business. After their first job pulling parts for customers in the company warehouse after school, they were trained in both sales and service. In 2001, their father passed along the company reins into their capable hands. The next year they expanded with a third location in Ft. Worth. Bane continues to provide quality equipment from North Texas throughout the United States. Bane Machinery provides equipment, parts, and service to nearly half the counties in Texas for contractors. Current governmental cooperative contracts extend options statewide and nationwide –see Governmental Sales for more details. The equipment brands we represent are dependable, with excellent performance records. Our extensive parts inventory assures quick availability, and our broad range of services help you maintain your equipment in top condition.

Alliance for Global Good is focused on developing strategies and best practices for effective collaboration to tackle complex global issues.
Full Description: The Alliance for Global Good was borne from the conviction that in the next fifty years, we must demand and ensure that we leave our children and grandchildren a world of hope rather than despair. Our world today is confronted with a multitude of global challenges in every area—health, education, environment, poverty, and global relations. Critically, these problems are measurable, substantial and growing over time. Take a look around the world: 4 billion people live on less than $4/day; 700 million adults cannot read; millions of children die each year of curable diseases because they lack access to clean water and basic healthcare; the environment is changing, perhaps irrevocably, and political sites of conflict around the globe erupt in violence every day. Take a look at the issues pervading American society: public education is mediocre; energy demands continue to grow; environmental challenges abound; health goals are not met; economic growth barely stirs as our recession strengthens glaring socioeconomic disparities. At the same time, studies demonstrate current weaknesses in philanthropic practices: At home, philanthropy is vigorous but uncertain, hopeful but diffuse. Nearly $100 billion is wasted each year due to duplication of efforts, competition for resources, and difficulty identifying best practice. Given the extensive challenges we face, we can’t afford to waste any philanthropic assets. We must identify best strategies to leverage resources and ensure that every dollar is used most effectively.

Industries: Consumer Electronics, Information Technology, Virtual Reality
Description: IonVR uses a custom optical technology system to nearly eliminate motion blur, creating the best available mobile VR experience today.
Full Description: Virtual Reality can change the world, and their Founder and lead inventor, Dan Thurber, saw that vision the minute he put on the Oculus DK1. Where most people put on a headset and are excited about the content, Dan put on the headset and wanted to know how he could improve it. For decades, Virtual Reality has been plagued by Sim Sickness, a kind of motion sickness that is induced by problems with motion blur and latency. (This is different from general motion sickness.) How could VR change the world if too many people were getting sick inside the headsets? How could Dan’s vision for virtual reality be realized if the VR Experience wasn’t optimized? This vision for virtual reality that Dan saw in 2013 wasn’t just cooler gaming. It was the way that virtual reality could continue the transformation of how they as people interact with content. This transformation has been underway since the early adoption of the personal computer and will continue well into the future. They no longer just consume content; they interact with it. And virtual reality will bring that interaction into a third, and more intimate, dimension. The IonVR team is already actively working on enterprise applications for VR, including medical devices and therapies, real estate, and manufacturing. Theyalso fundamentally believe that VR has the opportunity to connect people even further in their digital, social lives. This opportunity to better the world, to make an impact with new technology, is what drives the IonVR team each day to bring this product to life.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Hardware, Information Technology, Software

Description: Affordable Annuity And Life Insurance Sales Training… and Systems!
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Discover… The First Truly Dedicated Insurance Sales Trainers, Coaches and Mentors For Career and Independent Agents, Advisors and Multi Line Agents. We Are Strictly Insurance Sales Trainers, Coaches and Mentors for new and experienced advisors. We are NOT Recruiters!!! Our Mission… To help you... to help middle-income families to ‘find the money’ to spend, save, invest, insure and plan wisely for the future, to “Live Debt Free and Truly Wealthy!” Our Goal… To help you become the most recognized and sought after advisor in your local community! Our Philosophy… If you help enough people to get what they want, then you’ll get what you want! MessageLew Nason,,, Insurance Sales Trainer, coach and Mentor... "The 9 Out of 10 Guy" From Our Founder Lew Nason… Like most agents, I struggled when I started in insurance sales in 1982. But, then I got extremely lucky, because I had three very successful producers take me under their wings. First of all, they taught me how to consistently find and attract my ‘Ideal’ insurance leads, by getting a message out of how I was really helping people. Then, I learned how to ask the right questions. So, I was able to consistently set high-quality appointments and close sales with ‘9 out of 10’ of those ‘IDEAL’ insurance leads. As a result, I quickly became a top producer. (Thank You, Mike, Phil & Ron!) Then, over the years, my sons and I were very fortunate to meet and learn from many industry’s super achievers. Now, it’s my turn to give back to this great insurance industry. Accordingly, my family and I would like to pass all this vital insurance sales training on to you!  Lew Nason, RFC, LUTCF… “The 9 Out Of 10 Guy”, Insurance Sales Trainer, Coach… Mentor About the Insurance Pro Shop (IPS)… In December of 1999, my sons and I decided to open the Insurance Pro Shop! Because we recognized that most of the insurance sales trainers, companies, and IMOs were only teaching agents and advisors how to sell their products. When instead, they should have been teaching them how to really help people! So, in 1999 we became the first and only full service, insurance sales trainers strictly dedicated to helping individual insurance professionals. However, unlike most of the other insurance sales trainers today, we decided NOT to be recruiters in disguise! Now, for over 3 decades, my family has been training, coaching, mentoring and supporting ‘new’ and ‘experienced’ career and independent insurance agents, financial advisors, and Multi Line agents. From 1983-1999 as a manager and general agent, Lew recruited and trained hundreds of insurance agents and financial advisors. Then since 1999, as insurance sales trainers, coaches and mentors, the Insurance Pro Shop has helped thousands to successfully sell life insurance and annuities! The great news is… we have a proven record of helping our clients to dramatically increase their sales… In as little as 60 days! And it is because all those agents and advisors are now focusing on really helping their prospects, clients, friends, and family!

Full Description: Terrain offers the world’s first Algorithm Management Platform for e-commerce organizations.  Terrain offers a self-service approach to building, testing, deploying and optimizing e-commerce channels.  Users of Terrain get more clicks, conversions, and revenue with AI assisted merchandising, self-learning search, email personalization, and dynamic feed optimization. Terrain was founded in 2015 by Mike Agnich and Charles Tripp.  They noticed that many e-commerce professionals were struggling to implement algorithms to better manage their e-commerce channels.  While the marketers and channel managers knew what steps they needed to take to improve channel performance, they found that much of the technical capability required to optimize e-commerce offers were held by the IT teams.  Consequently, projects took longer, cost more and had a lower likelihood of succeeding than was ideal. Today, Terrain’s mission is to put algorithm success in the hands of e-commerce managers and marketers so they can drive improved performance, higher conversions and more profitability.   Our customers are seeing 5% - 20%+ improvements in key e-commerce conversion metrics, and are developing powerful new processes that allow them to challenge the most advanced competitors in their industries.

Description: We are Beep Industries - we make simple elegant objects that do one thing well.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Four people - Lou, Kate, Gina and Bren - are Beep Industries. We design our own original products which we then make and sell; after-all there's no point in thinking this stuff up if people can't actually play with it! So far we've made MoviePeg, MIXA and most recently POPA. Every single thing we make follows the Beep design ethos: simple and elegant objects that do one thing really well.  Beep was created in early 2011 by Brendan Dawes and Lou Cordwell in Manchester, UK. Eleven years earlier Lou and Bren started digital design company magneticNorth (mN) and in 2009 ventured into making their own products with MIXA - a digital mixtape. Over time, fuelled by blind enthusiasm and a second product called MoviePeg, Lou and Bren decided to form a new product focussed company and together with Kate and Gina they founded Beep Industries.  The Beep sketchbook is bursting with new ideas to remind people of things they've never seen before - new products, new takes on old products, limited editions and partnerships.

Full Description: BrainGate is a path to a better way of life for severely motor-impaired individuals. Through years of advanced research, BrainGate enables these people with the ability to communicate, interact and function through thought. (view video) BrainGate's mission is to further the advancement of this life-changing technology to promote wider adoption to help impaired individuals communicate and interact with society. For instance, the Cyberkenetics BrainGate Neural Interface is currently the subject of a pilot clinical trial being conducted under an Investigational Device Exemption (IDE) from the FDA. The system is designed to restore functionality for a limited, immobile group of severely motor-impaired individuals. It is expected that people using the BrainGate System will employ a personal computer as the gateway to a range of self-directed activities. These activities may extend beyond typical computer functions (e.g., communication) to include the control of objects in the environment such as a telephone, a television and lights.
